JAVASCRIPT LEARNING
javascript:A programming language that interracts with the browser making it interractive and responsive.

USES OF JAVASCRIPT
-User interractivity:How a user interracts with the pages,etc.
-Reactivity:automatic loading of data to a page.

Where to write javascript,we have internal javascript and external javascript
-internal javascript is inside HTML
-it can come in two ways:script stag,where u can have it in the head section or at the inside of body section,where it is the most common ones.
-external javascript is run using a source attribute <script src=""></script>

JAVASCRIPT VARIABLES.
-A container used to store values.

RULES FOR NAMING VARIABLES.
-Are identified with unique identifiers
-Rules for identifiers,variables can only begin with letters,underscores,dollar signs,underscores.
-variable names begin with letters,underscores,dollar signs.
-variable names are case sensitive
-words cant be reserved sensitive
